The paper discusses the progress made towards making a machine smart enough to pass standardized math and science tests, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and computer vision. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and computer vision (cs.CV).
